# Export map (linker version script) for the fluxd executable.
#
# fluxd is a standalone daemon launched as `fluxd daemon`. The kernel enters it at the
# ELF entry point (e_entry) — NOT through a dynamic symbol — so the executable needs to
# export no global symbols at all:
#
#   - it is not a shared library and nothing dlopen()s it;
#   - no JNI layer resolves symbols out of it (SynthesisCore is a separate APK run under
#     app_process, in its own process, and communicates through the telemetry file, not
#     through fluxd's symbol table);
#   - there is no externally documented ABI that consumers link against.
#
# So the required entry points are the ELF entry point and fluxd's imports from libc /
# libc++ — none of which is a *defined global* symbol of fluxd. Making every defined
# global local therefore removes the whole project-internal export surface (every
# `flux::…` symbol) from the dynamic symbol table without hiding anything fluxd needs to
# start or run. `local: *` only demotes *defined* globals; undefined imports are
# untouched, so the binary still links and executes.
#
# This is the authoritative export map referenced by LOCAL_LDFLAGS in jni/Android.mk.
# .github/scripts/verify-native-hardening.sh proves, from the built binary, that its
# dynamic table exports no `flux::` symbol — i.e. that this map took effect — while
# verify-native-telemetry.sh continues to prove (from the unstripped link output, whose
# .symtab and build-id this map does not touch) that every required V2 component is still
# linked in. Hiding a dynamic *export* is not hiding a component from the *link*.
{
  local:
    *;
};
